Ça serait intéressant s'il pouvait s'intégrer avec Google maps, de cette façon pour trouver une adresse celà pourrait être plus facile. Il reste des améliorations à faire avec l'application.

Information is good and very helpful. I would rate 5 stars if it was not of the code in background that's very bad. The app is slow, it freezes every time it refreshes.. and it refresh automatically everytime you toggle between apps and takes at least one minute to unfreeze!! Very annoying.
Sert absolument à rien! Les clubs ne font pas les mises à jour des sentiers.

L'application est fonctionnelle, mais elle comporte beaucoup trop de lenteurs et de gèles intermittent, ce qui rend l'expérience global désagréable. Il faut être patient pour que la carte se charge et parfois la carte gèle sans raison. Il faudrait avoir la possibilité de télécharger les cartes sur l'application directement et les mettres à jour au besoin. Cela là rendrait plus pratique quand on a aucune connexion et surtout la navigation serait instantané.
On se croirait ds une application développée en 2005... Manque d'information... Très lente... Peu agréable à utiliser... Désolant d'avoir payer ça

Very helpful 99% accurate only once was a discrepancy with the map. Very practical to calculate distances and establish the itinerary I did for 5 days. Also give good directions gas stations unfortunately not all of them are updated but in view of all the information available this is much better than even two years ago. However some of the pourvoirie websites where not accessible directly.all in all this is the best you can get out there.
Would be great if the app could connect to other people using the app.. could keep a close eye on people you come with and able to send messages

content: Good trip planner.
It's great. Nuff said.

If you are snowmobiling in Quebec this is an essential app.  While it doesn't list lots of gas stations and restaurants,  it does show the trail and where you are in real time.  This proved invaluable when I made a wrong turn and/or lost the trail.  You open the app, and it guides you back to the trail.  It literally saved hours of wasted time.  It also provides accurate mileage estimates by clicking on the start and finish points.  Lots of room for improvement,  but it is something everyone should get before hitting the trails.
Works well,takes a bit to find yourself when phone in air plane mode.Cheaper than getting a $$$300.00 gps.Great 1st version and helpful!!!

The grooming delay feature only seems to work when connected to the cellular network.  When I am connected to WiFi the app does allow me to click grooming delay but colored lines do not show up overlaid on the trails.
